  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes the component swizzle mapping for a Vulkan YCbCr sampler.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`GRVkYcbcrComponents` describes how the RGBA components of a Vulkan YCbCr sampler image
are swizzled when creating a `GRVkYcbcrConversionInfo`. Each property (`R`, `G`, `B`, `A`)
holds a Vulkan component swizzle value that maps a source channel to a destination channel.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var components = new GRVkYcbcrComponents
{
    R = 0u, // VK_COMPONENT_SWIZZLE_IDENTITY
    G = 0u, // VK_COMPONENT_SWIZZLE_IDENTITY
    B = 0u, // VK_COMPONENT_SWIZZLE_IDENTITY
    A = 0u, // VK_COMPONENT_SWIZZLE_IDENTITY
};
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
